Here's a React + Tailwind component that meets your requirements:

```jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect, useRef } from 'react';

const CopyButton = ({ text }) => {
  const [isCopied, setIsCopied] = useState(false);
  const timeoutRef = useRef(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    // Cleanup timeout on unmount
    return () => {
      if (timeoutRef.current) {
        clearTimeout(timeoutRef.current);
      }
    };
  }, []);

  const handleCopy = async () => {
    try {
      await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
      setIsCopied(true);

      // Clear any existing timeout
      if (timeoutRef.current) {
        clearTimeout(timeoutRef.current);
      }

      // Reset after 1.5 seconds
      timeoutRef.current = setTimeout(() => {
        setIsCopied(false);
        timeoutRef.current = null;
      }, 1500);
    } catch (err) {
      console.error('Failed to copy text:', err);
    }
  };

  return (
    <>
      <button
        onClick={handleCopy}
        className="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white bg-blue-600 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-blue-500 transition-all duration-200 disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed"
        aria-label={isCopied ? "Copied!" : "Copy to clipboard"}
        disabled={isCopied}
      >
        {isCopied ? (
          <>
            <svg
              className="w-5 h-5 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            >
              <path
                strokeLinecap="round"
                strokeLinejoin="round"
                strokeWidth={2}
                d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"
              />
            </svg>
            Copied!
          </>
        ) : (
          <>
            <svg
              className="w-5 h-5 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            >
              <path
                strokeLinecap="round"
                strokeLinejoin="round"
                strokeWidth={2}
                d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"
              />
            </svg>
            Copy
          </>
        )}
      </button>

      {/* ARIA live region for screen reader announcements */}
      <div
        role="status"
        aria-live="polite"
        aria-atomic="true"
        className="sr-only"
      >
        {isCopied && "Text copied to clipboard"}
      </div>
    </>
  );
};

export default CopyButton;
```

This component features:

1. **State Management**: Uses `useState` to track the copied state and `useRef` for timeout management
2. **Copy Functionality**: Uses the modern `navigator.clipboard.writeText()` API with async/await
3. **Visual Feedback**: Shows a checkmark icon and "Copied!" text when clicked
4. **Timing**: Reverts to the original state after exactly 1.5 seconds
5. **Accessibility**: 
   - Includes proper `aria-label` that updates based on state
   - Has an ARIA live region with `role="status"` and `aria-live="polite"` for screen reader announcements
   - The live region uses Tailwind's `sr-only` class to hide it visually but keep it available to screen readers
6. **Styling**: 
   - Uses Tailwind classes for a modern button appearance
   - Includes hover and focus states
   - Disables the button while showing the copied state
   - Smooth transitions between states
7. **Error Handling**: Catches and logs any clipboard API errors
8. **Cleanup**: Properly clears timeouts on unmount to prevent memory leaks

The button can be used simply by passing the text to copy:
```jsx
<CopyButton text="Hello, World!" />
```
